3. Results and discussion
3.1. Crack propagation images and processing
Representative images obtained from the high-speed camera are shown in Fig. 2 for test 1. The images show that the crack propagation occurred in the direction parallel to the pre-crack, which simplifies the velocity calculation in this work. It also confirms the overall mode I
loading and that the crack did not turn. Crack growth was observed to occur with rounding/blunting of the tip, consistent with past observations on crack growth in soft materials [6]. A custom macro for ImageJ [7] (provided as supplemental material) was used to process images by applying edge detection and thresholding to convert them to black and white (as shown in Fig. 3). A horizontal line representing the crack-tip path was identified and its end points are specified within the macro. The crack tip was identified as its
