growth. Also, PDMS is soft with nonlinear stress–strain response, which can lead to crack tip blunting. Since this method is image based, it becomes possible to characterize not only the tip location but also possible crack blunting due to material nonlinearity and softness around the crack tip. Future research could enhance this method by exploring the influence of factors like the size of the initial nick, preload amount, specimen width, and material stiffness on crack propagation. The method’s adaptability makes it well-suited for examining these variables in detail. Furthermore, incorporating high-speed imaging with computational tools like digital image correlation and finite element analysis may deepen the understanding of dynamic crack growth in soft materials.
